We have to go now.
Clark! We have to go.

764
00:57:08.100 --> 00:57:10.320
- It's gonna come back. it's gonna find me!
- Kat! Kat? Uh...

765
00:57:10.520 --> 00:57:12.930
Wait. I don't understand.
Wh-where are you?

766
00:57:13.310 --> 00:57:15.430
Please. let me the fuck in!

767
00:57:16.820 --> 00:57:18.340
But it's a... it's-it's a wall!

768
00:57:18.360 --> 00:57:19.700
How can-how can you see me?

769
00:57:21.400 --> 00:57:23.060
I'm on the other side of the glass.

770
00:57:23.480 --> 00:57:25.260
How can you not see me?

771
00:57:25.280 --> 00:57:27.720
What glass?! What the
fuck are you talking about?

772
00:57:28.420 --> 00:57:30.550
Wh-what are you talk--

773
00:57:30.600 --> 00:57:32.790
Okay. can you see
anything on your side?

774
00:57:32.810 --> 00:57:36.020
Can you see a handle. a
door? Is there a hatch. anything?

775
00:57:37.370 --> 00:57:38.710
No. no. no. no...

776
00:57:38.730 --> 00:57:42.590
Uh... Okay. Let me figure
this out. okay? Just hold on.

777
00:57:43.140 --> 00:57:45.270
Hold on. okay? It's just...

778
00:57:47.140 --> 00:57:49.080
- Clark?
- No. no. just let me...

779
00:57:49.300 --> 00:57:50.280
- Clark!
- Just hold on!

780
00:57:50.300 --> 00:57:52.390
- Let me figure this out!
- CLARK!

781
00:57:52.400 --> 00:57:53.370
- Let me figure this out...
- Clark! Clark!

782
00:57:53.390 --> 00:57:54.730
Clark. behind you!

783
00:59:11.760 --> 00:59:12.890
Mary!

784
00:59:24.350 --> 00:59:25.550
Mary...

785
00:59:26.330 --> 00:59:27.560
what were you thinking?

786
00:59:29.160 --> 00:59:31.090
I never. ever.

787
00:59:31.100 --> 00:59:32.950
ever said you could go outside.

788
00:59:34.970 --> 00:59:36.080
It's no good.

789
00:59:37.710 --> 00:59:39.410
They're all over the place.

790
01:00:56.150 --> 01:00:58.400
"Hi. you've reached Dr. Mary Klein."

791
01:00:58.410 --> 01:00:59.820
"I'm not able to answer the call.

792
01:00:59.830 --> 01:01:01.370
"so please leave a message.

793
01:01:01.380 --> 01:01:02.950
"and I'll get back to
you as soon as I can."

794
01:01:06.080 --> 01:01:07.080
"Mary...

795
01:01:10.340 --> 01:01:11.540
"I opened the window."

796
01:01:16.090 --> 01:01:18.060
"I won't be coming back."

797
01:02:03.020 --> 01:02:03.820
"...Please!"

798
01:02:05.610 --> 01:02:06.600
"Save us!"

799
01:02:06.960 --> 01:02:09.390
"All right! I'll do it!

800
01:02:09.410 --> 01:02:12.910
I'll save you! I will do it!"

801
01:02:23.010 --> 01:02:26.580
"Moon Child!"

802
01:02:27.010 --> 01:02:28.580
I don't know where that hand's been.

803
01:02:33.130 --> 01:02:35.780
"Well. ahoy there. mateys!"

804
01:02:35.790 --> 01:02:37.580
"Now. according to me map.

805
01:02:37.600 --> 01:02:41.240
"we've landed on the crystal
shores of a bountiful land.

806
01:02:41.250 --> 01:02:44.440
"a land filled with great deals."

807
01:02:44.460 --> 01:02:46.850
"So drop your anchors and come on down

808
01:02:46.870 --> 01:02:49.630
"to Cap'n Clark's Ottoman Empire."

809
01:02:49.650 --> 01:02:51.920
"Get lost in an endless sea

810
01:02:51.940 --> 01:02:55.780
"of quality tables. chairs.
couches. and bedroom sets."

811
01:02:55.790 --> 01:02:58.530
"Need bed bunks for the
scallywagses quarters?

812
01:02:58.540 --> 01:02:59.890
"W've got it all!"

813
01:02:59.910 --> 01:03:01.750
"And at prices so low

814
01:03:01.770 --> 01:03:03.430
"you'll think that yo're robbing me!"

815
01:03:33.530 --> 01:03:34.430
Hello?

816
01:03:46.220 --> 01:03:47.390
Hello?

817
01:03:55.260 --> 01:03:56.180
Clark?

818
01:04:09.540 --> 01:04:11.050
Clark. can you hear me?

819
01:04:50.130 --> 01:04:51.210
Clark?

820
01:07:45.930 --> 01:07:47.060
Clark?

821
01:10:29.730 --> 01:10:30.900
Clark?

822
01:10:34.060 --> 01:10:35.330
You found it.

823
01:10:43.940 --> 01:10:45.750
Why are you hiding?

824
01:10:47.830 --> 01:10:49.610
You were being too loud.

825
01:11:01.660 --> 01:11:03.180
Where are we?

826
01:11:06.170 --> 01:11:07.160
It's...

827
01:11:09.900 --> 01:11:12.300
...every place that ever was.

828
01:11:19.840 --> 01:11:21.640
How long have you been here?

829
01:11:28.140 --> 01:11:29.680
What was that?

830
01:11:35.170 --> 01:11:36.540
Stay calm.

831
01:11:41.040 --> 01:11:42.550
It's only me.

832
01:11:45.220 --> 01:11:46.740
You know me.

833
01:12:16.840 --> 01:12:18.270
I'm sorry.

834
01:12:19.900 --> 01:12:22.180
This is for your own good.

835
01:14:25.830 --> 01:14:27.640
As you walk through life.

836
01:14:28.130 --> 01:14:33.960
the untrained mind
accumulates loops. habits...

837
01:14:35.500 --> 01:14:40.110
...behaviors that keep
you drifting in circles.

838
01:14:41.040 --> 01:14:43.510
creating the same problems.

839
01:14:44.160 --> 01:14:46.830
reaching for the same solutions

840
01:14:47.830 --> 01:14:50.250
over and over again.

841
01:14:52.030 --> 01:14:56.760
Still. it's the neural
pathway of least resistance.

842
01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:02.820
The one I made.

843
01:15:02.830 --> 01:15:04.690
The one that kept me safe...

844
01:15:04.870 --> 01:15:06.480
when I was a child.

845
01:15:08.900 --> 01:15:10.500
You know...

846
01:15:11.120 --> 01:15:13.890
I learned to push people
away before they could hurt me.

847
01:15:15.240 --> 01:15:18.270
And. now. as an adult.

848
01:15:18.950 --> 01:15:23.100
I'm still stuck right where I started.

849
01:15:26.050 --> 01:15:27.550
Alone.

850
01:15:29.530 --> 01:15:30.760
What is this?

851
01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:35.760
It's a real mess. Am I right?

852
01:15:35.900 --> 01:15:37.300
Clark...

853
01:15:38.570 --> 01:15:39.740
...let me help you...

854
01:15:41.930 --> 01:15:43.760
before you do anything
you can't take back.

855
01:15:43.780 --> 01:15:45.240
Answer the question.

856
01:15:46.430 --> 01:15:49.020
Yes. it's a real mess.

857
01:15:51.690 --> 01:15:54.580
But also beautiful in a way.

858
01:15:55.060 --> 01:15:56.040
No?

859
01:16:03.760 --> 01:16:04.960
Who are these people?

860
01:16:07.170 --> 01:16:08.770
This place builds them.

861
01:16:09.280 --> 01:16:12.770
Oh. actually. more
like it remembers them.

862
01:16:14.250 --> 01:16:16.680
And the more times it
remembers something.

863
01:16:16.690 --> 01:16:18.180
the less it does.

864
01:16:19.410 --> 01:16:23.110
Somewhere out there
is a guy in a striped shirt.

865
01:16:23.120 --> 01:16:25.030
but. in here. he's...

866
01:16:26.980 --> 01:16:28.210
remembered.

867
01:16:28.950 --> 01:16:31.460
Just slightly wrong.

868
01:16:32.680 --> 01:16:34.540
Somewhere out there is a man

869
01:16:34.560 --> 01:16:36.990
in a wheelchair. and a lamp.

870
01:16:46.040 --> 01:16:48.220
I'm pretty sure that's
how you get all of this.

871
01:16:48.480 --> 01:16:50.380
You know. all these places

872
01:16:50.570 --> 01:16:53.410
and rooms and buildings

873
01:16:54.310 --> 01:16:55.870
misremembering themselves.

874
01:16:56.020 --> 01:16:57.350
Clark...

875
01:16:57.720 --> 01:16:59.120
let's talk this through.

876
01:17:00.260 --> 01:17:01.560
In some ways...

877
01:17:02.330 --> 01:17:04.840
they're an improvement
on the originals.

878
01:17:06.980 --> 01:17:08.350
For starters.

879
01:17:09.250 --> 01:17:10.780
they can't feel anything.

880
01:17:21.850 --> 01:17:23.780
Can you imagine how
good that must feel?

881
01:17:26.570 --> 01:17:27.860
I mean...

882
01:17:28.550 --> 01:17:32.050
...there's no thoughts
or pain. no ego...

883
01:17:33.580 --> 01:17:34.800
...no fear.

884
01:17:36.040 --> 01:17:37.580
They simply...

885
01:17:38.610 --> 01:17:39.950
exist.

886
01:17:40.970 --> 01:17:43.570
Like... like furniture!

887
01:17:46.620 --> 01:17:49.060
Look at this. The best part.

888
01:17:53.350 --> 01:17:54.460
You can eat them!

889
01:18:36.680 --> 01:18:38.180
That's my. uh...

890
01:18:38.210 --> 01:18:39.840
assistant manager.

891
01:18:42.360 --> 01:18:44.270
I tried to help her.
but she just. uh...

892
01:18:45.070 --> 01:18:46.340
Clark!

893
01:18:47.380 --> 01:18:50.550
If you untie me. we
can talk this through.

894
01:18:50.860 --> 01:18:52.080
get you feeling better.

895
01:18:52.090 --> 01:18:53.840
Yeah. well. what if I did untie you?

896
01:18:53.850 --> 01:18:55.320
You know. what then?

897
01:18:55.650 --> 01:18:57.040
You'd run around here

898
01:18:57.050 --> 01:18:58.550
like a chicken with its head cut off.

899
01:18:58.570 --> 01:18:59.820
looking for a way out.

900
01:19:00.770 --> 01:19:03.250
But you'd end up in the
same place you are now.

901
01:19:04.530 --> 01:19:07.030
Like the path thing you're
always talking about.

902
01:19:07.830 --> 01:19:09.160
Clark!

903
01:19:09.610 --> 01:19:12.150
I just want to help you.
Just tell me what you need.

904
01:19:13.150 --> 01:19:14.780
I'll-I'll-I'll do it.

905
01:19:16.670 --> 01:19:17.380
Yeah?

906
01:19:17.400 --> 01:19:19.400
Yeah. Yes. please.

907
01:19:22.500 --> 01:19:23.500
Okay.

908
01:19:25.770 --> 01:19:27.160
Well. I want you to tell me

909
01:19:27.180 --> 01:19:28.850
that I didn't do anything
wrong. you know.

910
01:19:28.860 --> 01:19:30.640
that-that you were wrong about me.

911
01:19:30.660 --> 01:19:33.300
I was wrong about you! I was.

912
01:19:33.320 --> 01:19:35.730
- I was wrong about you.
- No. no. not-not like that.

913
01:19:36.980 --> 01:19:38.840
Not... not so fast. okay?

914
01:19:40.250 --> 01:19:42.320
I mean. I wanna... I
want to set the scene first!

915
01:19:46.400 --> 01:19:48.740
Let's start. um...

916
01:19:49.550 --> 01:19:51.020
well. the night that. uh...

917
01:19:51.810 --> 01:19:54.820
that I got kicked out of my own house.

918
01:19:54.940 --> 01:19:55.680
Yeah?

919
01:19:58.620 --> 01:20:00.420
It was. um... It was late.

920
01:20:01.840 --> 01:20:03.410
A lot darker.

921
01:20:04.240 --> 01:20:05.050
Uh...

922
01:20:07.720 --> 01:20:08.810
Lights. please.

923
01:20:19.330 --> 01:20:20.550
I tried this exercise with her before.

924
01:20:20.560 --> 01:20:22.780
It doesn't go anywhere.

925
01:20:24.210 --> 01:20:25.260
Fine!

926
01:20:25.740 --> 01:20:27.260
I'll do it myself.

927
01:20:27.970 --> 01:20:29.810
It's still my house after all.

928
01:20:33.470 --> 01:20:34.600
Yeah.

929
01:20:36.340 --> 01:20:37.850
Thank you. Much better.

930
01:20:39.660 --> 01:20:40.860
But there's...

931
01:20:41.780 --> 01:20:42.630
still...

932
01:20:43.940 --> 01:20:45.320
something off.

933
01:21:03.240 --> 01:21:04.840
Clark. please...

934
01:21:36.860 --> 01:21:39.390
No. please. don't. don't...!

935
01:21:57.890 --> 01:21:58.930
I'm sorry.

936
01:22:02.110 --> 01:22:03.050
I'm sorry. I...

937
01:22:04.590 --> 01:22:07.790
broke the glass and woke you up.

938
01:22:10.230 --> 01:22:12.240
I know how you like to sleep early.

939
01:22:16.530 --> 01:22:18.370
I was at the store late.

940
01:22:20.190 --> 01:22:22.270
I guess I lost track of the time.

941
01:22:25.060 --> 01:22:26.720
I was checking inventory.

942
01:22:27.280 --> 01:22:28.160
But...

943
01:22:28.900 --> 01:22:30.980
I stopped off for a few beers.

944
01:22:30.990 --> 01:22:32.530
- Clark--
- Barbara!

945
01:22:34.280 --> 01:22:36.250
I was checking inventory.

946
01:22:38.110 --> 01:22:40.250
Then I stopped off for a few beers.

947
01:22:45.160 --> 01:22:47.130
Defi-define a few.

948
01:22:47.150 --> 01:22:48.650
As many as I wanted.

949
01:22:50.070 --> 01:22:51.440
Because this is my house.

950
01:22:53.110 --> 01:22:54.480
I pay for it.

951
01:22:55.670 --> 01:22:58.350
I pay for everything. I
pay for you to go to school.

952
01:22:59.530 --> 01:23:01.170
I pay for your time off school!

953
01:23:01.930 --> 01:23:03.860
I pay for the roof over your head!

954
01:23:05.600 --> 01:23:07.000
You want kids. right?

955
01:23:07.720 --> 01:23:08.970
Well. that takes money.

956
01:23:08.990 --> 01:23:10.480
So someone has to work around here.

957
01:23:12.760 --> 01:23:13.970
I said someone has

958
01:23:13.970 --> 01:23:15.970
to get off her fat ass
and work around here!

959
01:23:16.720 --> 01:23:18.930
Just because you didn't
get to be an architect don--

960
01:23:18.940 --> 01:23:20.670
I am a fucking architect.

961
01:23:22.110 --> 01:23:24.600
I'm just stuck selling shit
furniture because someone

962
01:23:24.610 --> 01:23:27.360
won't get off her fat
fucking ass and help me!

963
01:23:27.370 --> 01:23:29.430
- I'm not your wife!
- Stay in character.

964
01:23:30.480 --> 01:23:31.350
Stay in character!

965
01:23:31.370 --> 01:23:33.580
- I've never even met her!
- STAY IN CHARACTER!

966
01:23:33.590 --> 01:23:35.290
FUCK YOU!

967
01:23:38.210 --> 01:23:39.020
What did you say?

968
01:23:39.030 --> 01:23:41.840
You wanna know the real
reason your wife left you?

969
01:23:41.850 --> 01:23:43.490
It wasn't the drinking.

970
01:23:43.500 --> 01:23:47.110
or the stumbling home
at all hours. or the rage.

971
01:23:47.120 --> 01:23:49.040
It was the whining!

972
01:23:49.050 --> 01:23:51.230
Nothing's ever your fault. is it?

973
01:23:51.400 --> 01:23:53.460
You drink too much? Blame your job.

974
01:23:53.660 --> 01:23:56.380
You hate your job? Blame the world.

975
01:23:56.440 --> 01:23:57.880
You get kicked out of the house?

976
01:23:57.900 --> 01:23:59.680
Blame your wife.

977
01:23:59.700 --> 01:24:01.720
You attack me and tie me up?

978
01:24:02.060 --> 01:24:03.280
Blame your brain!

979
01:24:03.290 --> 01:24:05.920
You are your fucking
brain. you dipshit!

980
01:24:10.400 --> 01:24:12.700
- You're saying it's my fault?
- Yes!

981
01:24:12.720 --> 01:24:15.040
But it's just the way
you're wired. isn't it?

982
01:24:15.050 --> 01:24:16.320
ISN'T IT?!

983
01:24:24.830 --> 01:24:26.560
How do I stop doing that?

984
01:24:27.470 --> 01:24:30.070
Honestly. I have no fucking idea.

985
01:24:32.730 --> 01:24:34.170
I can't help you. Clark.

986
01:24:35.030 --> 01:24:36.700
As much as I tried.

987
01:24:38.470 --> 01:24:39.920
It's just not up to me.

988
01:24:43.490 --> 01:24:44.850
I can't save anyone.

989
01:24:54.840 --> 01:24:56.030
You know...

990
01:24:58.830 --> 01:25:00.570
I don't think I want to change.

991
01:25:03.580 --> 01:25:04.820
Then don't.

992
01:25:11.980 --> 01:25:13.590
I like it in here.

993
01:25:18.040 --> 01:25:19.770
For the first time in a long time.

994
01:25:19.790 --> 01:25:21.310
I feel like I'm...

995
01:25:24.800 --> 01:25:27.950
like I'm right where
I'm supposed to be.

996
01:25:30.680 --> 01:25:32.130
Then stay.

997
01:25:34.140 --> 01:25:35.140
Right where you are.

998
01:25:39.990 --> 01:25:41.000
But let me go.

999
01:26:10.820 --> 01:26:12.020
I'm sorry.

1000
01:26:15.900 --> 01:26:17.000
About what?

1001
01:26:48.030 --> 01:26:49.630
What are you doing in here?

1002
01:26:56.020 --> 01:26:57.720
This is Mary.

1003
01:26:58.990 --> 01:27:00.800
She's our therapist.

1004
01:27:02.340 --> 01:27:03.710
She was just leaving.

1005
01:27:06.000 --> 01:27:07.390
No. no.

1006
01:27:08.110 --> 01:27:09.650
You don't have to worry.

1007
01:27:11.510 --> 01:27:13.550
She says we don't need to change.

1008
01:27:25.930 --> 01:27:27.030
It's okay.

1009
01:27:28.820 --> 01:27:30.890
It's just the way we're wired.

1010
01:31:24.480 --> 01:31:26.940
[Ganda (Luganda)] "Greetings
to all peoples of the universe...

1011
01:31:26.950 --> 01:31:29.040
[Ganda (Luganda)] "God
give you peace always."

1012
01:31:29.060 --> 01:31:37.510
[Marathi] "Greetings. The people of the Earth send their
good wishes and hope you find good fortune in this life."

1013
01:31:37.730 --> 01:31:41.580
[Amoy] "Friends from
space. how are you all?

1014
01:31:41.590 --> 01:31:45.280
[Amoy] "Have you eaten yet?
Come visit us if you have time."

1015
01:31:46.920 --> 01:31:48.080
No...

1016
01:31:55.570 --> 01:31:58.690
[Czech] "Dear Friends.
we wish you the best."

1017
01:31:58.870 --> 01:32:02.450
[Kannada] "Greetings. On behalf of
Kannada-speaking people. 'good wishes'."

1018
01:32:02.560 --> 01:32:06.920
[Rajasthani] "Hello to everyone...

1019
01:32:06.930 --> 01:32:09.130
[Rajasthani] "We are happy
here and you be happy there."

1020
01:32:09.140 --> 01:32:12.220
"Hello from the
children of planet Earth."

1021
01:32:17.180 --> 01:32:24.160
[Ancient Greek] "Greetings to you. whoever you
are. We come in friendship to those who are friends."

1022
01:32:24.290 --> 01:32:27.260
[Portuguese] "Peace and
happiness to everyone."

1023
01:32:32.650 --> 01:32:35.070
[Akkadian] "May all be very well."

1024
01:32:36.050 --> 01:32:38.680
[Russian] "Greetings! I welcome you!"

1025
01:32:39.090 --> 01:32:41.940
[Thai] "Hello friends from..."

1026
01:32:56.320 --> 01:32:58.160
[French] "Hello. everyone."

1027
01:35:16.210 --> 01:35:17.790
Are you okay? Are you okay?

1028
01:35:17.800 --> 01:35:18.900
Who the fuck is that?

1029
01:35:18.920 --> 01:35:20.220
Who is it?

